Everything was outstanding! We were celebrating my mom‚Äôs birthday and they had a card waiting for her at the table. We started with the calamari, roasted garlic w/ grilled bread, and blue cheese ‚Äúcookies‚Äù. I had the best crab cake I‚Äôve ever eaten as my entree. Everyone else thoroughly enjoyed their food, too. The owner stopped by and chatted with us, and even brought out fruit and crackers for our toddler. We‚Äôll definitely return!

Had an absolutely wonderful dinner at Rococo on Western and the taste was amazing! This upscale seafood restaurant truly delivers on both presentation and flavor. The seafood pasta was phenomenal - perfectly cooked shrimp and what appeared to be lobster or crab over delicate angel hair in a rich, creamy sauce, with fresh dill that added a lovely herbal note complementing the seafood beautifully. The clams were fresh and briny, cooked just right, and even the soup was expertly prepared with great depth of flavor. The plating is restaurant-quality beautiful with expertly crafted martinis that were clean and well-balanced. Everything about the experience felt upscale and refined - you can tell they use quality ingredients and have skilled preparation. This is definitely a place I'll be returning to, and for seafood lovers in OKC, Rococo on Western is a must-try. The combination of exceptional flavors, beautiful presentation, and upscale atmosphere makes it a standout dining destination that I highly recommend for special occasions or when you want to treat yourself to outstanding seafood!

We went in for an early dinner around 5pm on Saturday. No wait time! Server was phenomenal  with services. Extremely knowledgeable, came to check on us every step of way. Bartender even made us a fruity micktail that was not on menu. We ordered Grilled cheese sandwiches with fries for kids. We started with Sharkuterie which is great is you want a sample of most like
shark sausage, seared tuna, salmon
pastrami, snow crab claws, octopus. For main we had catch of the day which was red fish blackened on a red of dirty rice and charred broccolini. Also had Lamb T- Bones with couscous. These two were decent but not memorable, seemed to be lacking some flavor somewhere. For dessert we had the chocolate. mousse which was pretty good! Overall great atmosphere, freshest sea food and great service! Would recommend.

This was my first time at Rococo and I was thoroughly impressed. From the ambience, to the staff, to the culinary direction. The cocktails offered were exquisite.¬† An afternoon lunch, dinner date, or group gathering seems perfect. I bet their brunch is superb. I highly recommend the mussels, grilled salmon, lobster sandwich and their s'more trifle, watch out!

Five stars aren't enough.

I just revisited Rococo on Western‚Äîmy first time back in years‚Äîand the crab cake nearly brought me to tears. I've never seen anyone treat seafood with this much respect. It's more than food; it's a work of art.

I used to work here, and Bruce and Jason were the best bosses I‚Äôve ever had. They treated their team like family, and that same warmth shows in every dish and every guest interaction. The wine list is top-notch, the food is true fine dining, and the vibe is unforgettable.

If you care about food‚Äîeven a little‚Äîyou owe yourself a visit.
